{"lemma":"أُسٌّ","slug":"أُسٌّ","root":"#.س.س","root_slug":"_-س-س","root_link":"/words/roots/_-س-س","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n715","n716","n717","n797","n810"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8F%D8%B3%D9%8C%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"foundation, groundwork, basis"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"power, exponent"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"remain, relic, trace, vestige, mark left","tags":["Classical"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Related words include Aramaic אוּשָּׁא (ʾūšā, “foundation”) as well as Akkadian 𒀳 (uššu, “foundation”), Akkadian 𒁼 (išdu, “base, foundation, root”), Akkadian 𒆠𒆗 (sassu, “base, floor”), Hebrew יְסוֹד (yəsōḏ, “foundation”), Aramaic אִיסָדָא (ʾĕsāḏā, “thing placed beneath, at the base or bottom; pillow”), Sabaean 𐩱𐩯 (ʾs³, “foundation”), Arabic اِسْت (ist), أَسَاس (ʔasās), سُدَّة (sudda) and وِسَادَة (wisāda, “pillow”). The verb Arabic أَسَّسَ (ʔassasa) and its reflexive Arabic تَأَسَّسَ (taʔassasa) are likely denominals of this noun, itself likely also borrowed wholly or semantically from the Aramaic.\nCompare the verbs Arabic شَيَّدَ (šayyada, “to establish firmly, build high”) and Hebrew שָׁת (šāṯ, “to place, lay down, put down”), as well as Arabic شَدَّ (šadda, “to strengthen, make firm, make strong”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n715","headword_ar":"اَسٌّ","root":"As","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see what next follows, in six places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n716","headword_ar":"اُسٌّ","root":"As","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"foundation, basis,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lowest part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh, Msb, K,) of a building, (S, A, K,) or of a wall; (Mgh, Msb;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^as~N","text_ar":"اَسٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_is~N","text_ar":"اـِسٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asaAsN","text_ar":"اَسَاسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asasN","text_ar":"اَسَسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) which is a contraction of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asaAsN","text_ar":"اَسَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"commencement"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a building: and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any commencement"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a thing; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^as~N","text_ar":"اَسٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asaAsN","text_ar":"اَسَاسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asasN","text_ar":"اَسَسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"origin, source, stock,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"root,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSol","text_ar":"اَصْل"},{"kind":"text","text":",) of a man; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^as~N","text_ar":"اَسٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": or of anything; (M, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^as~N","text_ar":"اَسٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_is~N","text_ar":"اـِسٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asiysN","text_ar":"اَسِيسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heart"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a man; because [the Arabs believe that] it is the first thing that comes into existence in the womb: (M, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=saAsN","text_ar":"ا=سَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Mgh, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_isaAsN","text_ar":"اـِسَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ususN","text_ar":"اُسُسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M, Mgh, Msb, K;) the first of which is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^Ns~N","text_ar":"اٌسٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb,) like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aqofaAlN","text_ar":"اَقْفَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qufolN","text_ar":"قُفْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) or of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asasN","text_ar":"اَسَسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asobaAbN","text_ar":"اَسْبَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sababN","text_ar":"سَبَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) or, as some say, of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ususN","text_ar":"اُسُسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEonaAqN","text_ar":"اَعْنَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EunuqN","text_ar":"عُنُقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] so that it is a pl. pl.; (TA;) and the second, of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^as~N","text_ar":"اَسٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EisaAsN","text_ar":"عِسَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eus~N","text_ar":"عُسٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) and the third, of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asaAsN","text_ar":"اَسَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb,) like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EunuqN","text_ar":"عُنُقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EanaAqN","text_ar":"عَنَاقٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aw~ali","text_ar":"الاَوَّلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"banaY bayotahu EalaY A^asaAsihi","text_ar":"بَنَى بَيْتَهُ عَلَى اَسَاسِهِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He built his house upon its first foundation."},{"kind":"text","text":"] (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qalaEahu mino A^us~ihi","text_ar":"قَلَعَهُ مِنْ اُسِّهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He uprooted it from its foundation"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amorihi Alka*ibu","text_ar":"اَمْرِهِ الكَذِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN A^asaAsu","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ اَسَاسُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one, the foundation of his affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"case, is falsehood"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAna *`laka EalaY A^us~i Ald~ahori","text_ar":"كَانَ ذٰلَكَ عَلَى اُسِّ الدَّهْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, A, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asihi","text_ar":"اَسِهِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_isihi","text_ar":"اـِسِهِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That was in old,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ancient, time;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at the beginning of time;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, * K;) and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealay A@soti","text_ar":"عَلَي ا@سْتِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~ahori","text_ar":"الدَّهْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A.) ―         -b2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A remain, relic, trace, vestige, sign, mark,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"track,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of anything. (K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xu*o A^us~a AlT~ariyqi","text_ar":"خُذْ اُسَّ الطَّرِيقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~ariyqi","text_ar":"الطَّرِيقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^as~a","text_ar":"اَسَّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [accord. to different copies of the K, meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Take thou to the track of the way,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] when one guides himself by any mark or track, or by camels' dung: but when the way is manifest, you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xu*o $araka AlT~ariyqi","text_ar":"خُذْ شَرَكَ الطَّرِيقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^us~N","text_ar":"اُسٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"remains of ashes"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"between the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^avaAfiY","text_ar":"اَثَافِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", q.v.: (M:) occurring in a verse of En-Nábighah Edh-Dhubyánee; but accord. to most relates of this verse, it is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=sN","text_ar":"ا=سٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","Mgh","Msb","K","M"]},{"entry_id":"n717","headword_ar":"اـِسٌّ","root":"As","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^us~N","text_ar":"اُسٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in several places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n797","headword_ar":"اَسٍ","root":"Asw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asowaAnu","text_ar":"اَسْوَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n810","headword_ar":"اَسٍ","root":"AsY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", [agreeably with analogy, as part. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asiYa","text_ar":"اَسِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] (M,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=sK","text_ar":"ا=سٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asiY~N","text_ar":"اَسِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asoyaAnu","text_ar":"اَسْيَانُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, K,) a dial. var. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asowaAnu","text_ar":"اَسْوَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA, [see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Asw","text_ar":"اسو"},{"kind":"text","text":"])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Grieving, mourning,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sorrowful:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Msb, K:) fem. [of the first, or second,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asiyapN","text_ar":"اَسِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=siyapN","text_ar":"ا=سِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and [of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AsyAn","text_ar":"اسيان"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asoyaAnapN","text_ar":"اَسْيَانَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asayoY","text_ar":"اَسَيْى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) pl. [of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AsyAn","text_ar":"اسيان"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asoyaAnuwna","text_ar":"اَسْيَانُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asaAyuwna","text_ar":"اَسَايُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is extr. and somewhat doubtful] (K) and [of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AsyAnp","text_ar":"اسيانة"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asoyaAnaAtN","text_ar":"اَسْيَانَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AsyY","text_ar":"اسيى"},{"kind":"text","text":"or of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asiyapN","text_ar":"اَسِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asaAyaA","text_ar":"اَسَايَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) and [of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AsyY","text_ar":"اسيى"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asoyayaAtN","text_ar":"اَسْيَيَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)"}],"source_refs":["M","K","Msb","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D8%A3%D8%B3/","headword_ar":"أس","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_32","lexicon_en":"Supplément aux dictionnaires arabes by Reinhart Dozy (d. 1883 CE)","lexicon_ar":"تكملة المعاجم العربية لرينهارت دوزي","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=10650#4636ea","body_html":"أس: لا، ما، لن (فوك) ويقال: ايس."},{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_32","lexicon_en":"Supplément aux dictionnaires arabes by Reinhart Dozy (d. 1883 CE)","lexicon_ar":"تكملة المعاجم العربية لرينهارت دوزي","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=10650#241f20","body_html":"أس: في ورق اللعب ذات اللامة الواحدة، يقال مثلا: أس الديناري (بوشر)."},{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_31","lexicon_en":"Al-Rāghib al-Isfahānī, al-Mufradāt fī Gharīb al-Qurʾān (d. c. 1109 CE)","lexicon_ar":"المفردات في غريب القرآن للراغب الأصفهاني","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=10650#f27689","body_html":"<span class=\"title1\">أس</span><span>َ</span><br><span>أَسَّسَ بنيانه: جعل له أُسّاً، وهو قاعدته التي يبتنى عليها، يقال: أُسٌّ وأَسَاسٌ، وجمع الأس:</span><br><span>إِسَاسٌ ، وجمع الإساس: أُسُس، يقال: كان ذلك على أسّ الدهر ، كقولهم: على وجه الدهر.</span>"},{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_3","lexicon_en":"Al-Khalīl b. Aḥmad al-Farāhīdī, Kitāb al-ʿAin (d. 786 CE)","lexicon_ar":"كتاب العين للخليل بن أحمد الفراهيدي","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=10650#329c0d","body_html":"<span>أس: الرّاقون إِذا رَقَوا الحيّة ليأخذوها ففرغ أحدهم من رُقْيته قال لها: أُسْ فتخضع وتلين. والأُسُّ: أصل تأسيس البناء، والجميع: الإِساس، وفي لغة: الأَسَس، والجميع: الآساس، ممدود. وأسٌ الرّماد: ما بقي في الموقد، قال:</span><br><br><span>فلم يبق إلاّ آلُ خَيْمٍ مُنَصَّبٍ </span><span class=\"red\">...</span><span> وسُفعٌ على أُسٍّ ونُؤْيٌ مُعَثلَبُ </span><br><br><span>وأسَّسْت داراً: بنيتُ حُدُودَها، ورفعت من قواعدها، ويُقال: هذا تأسيسٌ حَسَن. والتَّأسيسُ في الشِّعْر أَلفٌ تلزم القافية وبينها وبينَ أَحرُف الرَّوِيّ حرف يجوز رفعه وكَسْرُه ونَصْبُه، نحو: مَفاعِلنْ، فلو جاء مثل (محمّد) في قافية لم يكن فيه تَأْسيس، حتّى يكون نحو: مُجاهد، فالألف تأسيسُه، وإن جاء شيء من غير تأسيس فهو المؤسّس، وهو عيبٌ في الشِّعر، غير أنّه ربّما اضطُرَّ إليه، وأحسن ما يكون ذلك إذا كان الحرفُ الذّي بعد الألف مفتوحاً، لأن فتحته تغلب على فتحة الألف، كأنّها تُزال من الوهم، كما قال العجّاج :</span><br><br><span>مُبارَكٌ للأَنبياء خاتَمُ </span><span class=\"red\">...</span><span> مُعَلِّمٌ آيَ الهدى معلم</span><span> </span><span>فلو قال خاتِم بكسر التّاء لم يَحْسُنْ.</span>"}]}}